16 application for additional creditable service, is amended by redesignating subsection (e) as
17 subsection (f) and adding a new subsection (e) to read as follows:
18 "(e)(1) A member or former member of the General Assembly may make an irrevocable
19 election to become a member of this retirement system and may obtain creditable service
20 for prior service as a member of the General Assembly as provided in this Code section.
21 In order to obtain such additional creditable service, the member or former member must:
22 (A) Have served, at the time of the application, at least four years or two full terms as
23 a member of the General Assembly;
24 (B) Have never been a member of the Georgia Legislative Retirement System;
25 (C) Submit an application to the board of trustees in such manner as the board deems
26 appropriate; and
27 (D) Pay to the board of trustees an amount determined by the board of trustees to be
28 sufficient to cover the full actuarial cost of granting the creditable service as provided
29 in this Code section. Such payment shall be made in conjunction with the member's
30 application for membership;
31 (2) Notwithstanding paragraph (1) of this subsection, no creditable service shall be
32 granted or obtained pursuant to this subsection if such service may be used to calculate
33 creditable service under any other public retirement system created by this title.
34 (3) By September 1, 2026, the Employees' Retirement System shall send a onetime
35 notice to all members or former members of the General Assembly who meet the above
36 criteria. Such notice shall:
37 (A) Be in writing;
38 (B) Be sent via United States mail to the member's last known mailing address;
39 (C) Advise the member that he or she is eligible to retroactively become a member of
40 the Georgia Legislative Retirement System for past years or past terms served; and
