41 (D) Communicate the exact amount required to be paid pursuant to subparagraph (D)
42 of paragraph (1) of this subsection, in order for a member or former member to receive
43 creditable service in the Georgia Legislative Retirement System.
44 (4) Any member of the General Assembly who obtains creditable service for prior
45 service as a member of the General Assembly pursuant to paragraph (1) of this
46 subsection, whose service concluded before January 1, 2022, shall receive the monthly
47 pension amount provided in subsection (d) of Code Section 47-6-80.
48 (5) Any member of the General Assembly who obtains creditable service for prior
49 service as a member of the General Assembly pursuant to paragraph (1) of this
50 subsection, whose service concluded on or after January 1, 2022, shall receive the
51 monthly pension amount provided in subsection (c.1) of Code Section 47-6-80."
52 SECTION 2.
53 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2026, only if it is determined to have been
54 concurrently funded as provided in Chapter 20 of Title 47 of the Official Code of Georgia
55 Annotated, the "Public Retirement Systems Standards Law"; otherwise, this Act shall not
56 become effective and shall be automatically repealed in its entirety on July 1, 2026, as
57 required by subsection (a) of Code Section 47-20-50.
58 SECTION 3.
59 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
